items.name: Ivana Baquero (JG)
items.description:
Ivana Baquero is a Spanish actress, mainly known for her roles as Ofelia in Guillermo del Toro's film Pan's Labyrinth (which she played when she was just 11) and as Eretria in the TV show The Shannara Chronicles.

120-step TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (iv4n4b4quero:0.99), a woman as a movie star, modelshoot style, (extremely detailed CG unity 8k wallpaper), photo of the most beautiful artwork in the world, professional majestic oil painting by Ed Blinkey, Atey Ghailan, Studio Ghibli, by Jeremy Mann, Greg Manchess, Antonio Moro, trending on ArtStation, trending on CGSociety, Intricate, High Detail, Sharp focus, dramatic, photorealistic painting art by midjourney and greg rutkowski, (white turtleneck top:1.2), ((movie premiere)), (long skirt), ((standing near a movie theater)), ((paparazzi in the background)), (looking at viewer:1.2), (detailed pupils:1.3), ((closeup portrait:1.1))"

items.name: Serena - Aku no onna kanbu
items.description:
Serena from Aku no onna kanbu

UPDATE: Added "V2" version

  • Trained with Anime (final-full-pruned) model.

  • 4 versions; V2 (fixed quality without the need of extra tools), 6 epochs for less rectriction to the original artstyle and activation tags, and 9 & 10 epochs for a closer accuracy to the character.

  • Recommended LoRA weights; 0.6-1

  • Works best with ALL, MIDD, OUTD, and OUTALL LoRA weight blocks.

  • Activation tags: serena (aku no onna kanbu) or serena_aku_onna to get the character's traits, and serena_ova_bikini to the character's bikini outfit used briefly at the beach OVA.

    • serena_aku_onna (V2): Use alongside tail and wolf tail if you want her with a tail.

    • serena (aku no onna kanbu) (6, 9, and 10 epochs): Use alongside short hair and yellow eyes to get the character as much accurate as possible.

    • serena_ova_bikini: Use alongside yellow shorts, short shorts, bikini shorts.

  • In order to get other outfits that aren't accessed with serena_ova_bikini, you can try any of the following:

    • Place (yellow bikini:1.2), (strapless:1.2), (strapless bikini:1.2) in the "Negative Prompt" box.

    • Increase the weights of tags used for the desired outfit. ex; (blue shirt:1.2), (red skirt:1.2)

    • Use the OUTALL LoRA weight blocks for this LoRA.

    • Use the Inpainting functions to correct any "mistake" in the images, or to draw a piece of clothing over the initial image.

      • Generate a image of the character nude first, then with Photoshop or img2img's sketch/inpaint sketch draw any pieces of clothing like lingerie, bikini, etc. Then process that with img2img's inpainting.

    • In the txt2img tab use the hires fix function starting with a lower LoRA weight then changing into a higher weight in the function's prompt box.

items.description:
This is the twelfth model in my God series.

You can find all the models at GOD-OF-GREED, GOD-OF-ENVY, GOD-OF-LOVE, GOD-OF-ANIME, GOD-OF-LUST, GOD-OF-JUSTICE, GOD-OF-TIME, GOD-OF-FANTASY, GOD-OF-JOY, GOD-OF-HORROR, GOD-OF-PRIDE, GOD-OF-PUNK, GOD-OF-STORMS, GOD-OF-EUPHORIA, GOD-OF-GLUTTONY, GOD-OF-THE-WEST, GOD-OF-BEAUTY, GOD-OF-SEDUCTION, and GOD-OF-PEACE.

This model is a mix of multiple models from my GOD series, including ANIME, ENVY, TIME, FANTASY, and JOY. I also added a few lora files at low strength that add gold accents and jewels to the images to add a sense of opulence for the greed aspect of the model.

The model has Blessed2 VAE baked into it, so no VAE required.

All of the images I upload for this model are unedited and don't use any special extensions like ControlNet. I do not do any inpainting or img2img to correct errors. Why? Because you deserve to see how the model works without any touchup or special extensions like ControlNet. You can surely get better images by putting in the extra work, which I do for my personal images. The samples are just meant to showcase what the model can do raw with nothing but prompt engineering.

items.name: LomoStyle
items.description:
Lomostyle is the teaser for a future model. Trained on a subset of images and manual captions for the full dataset for testing, this model proved to be competent enough on it's own to justify a release.

So, what is it?
Lomostyle is nod to analog/lo-fi photography. Of which, the most consistent commonalities is the use of film over digital. This can be black and white film, reverse color, color negative, ect.. combined with cross processing techniques that would involve physical manipulation of the film. Overall, you can think of the aesthetic as being 'vintage'.

Requirements :

VAE Required: Download here

Install :

stable-diffusion-webui -> models -> VAE

In Webui :

Under Settings -> Stable Diffusion -> SD VAE select the downloaded VAE and uncheck Ignore selected VAE for stable diffusion checkpoints that have their own .vae.pt next to them

Usage :

Prompt Format : a <angle> <shot size> photo of <<prefix> <nationality> <subject> with <hair length -> color -> style> hair with <skin color> doing <thing + setting>>, <face features: such as "perfect face", "detailed facial features", makeup, ect..>, looking <direction> viewer>, wearing <clothing: if any>, <body type>, <breast size>, <ass size>, <exposed <body part>>, <skin details>, <lighting>, film grain, photographed on a <camera>, <lens: mm + aperture>, with <specific film>, <indoors/outdoors>, in/at <location>, <specific city>, <country>, during the <time of day>, sfw/nsfw, in lomostyle

Note: If that seems confusing or convoluted; look at the prompts in the sample images for better guidance.

Note Deux : Not all tags need be added if not applicable to what you're trying to create.

Example of caption from database :

a closeup portrait photo of a Russian woman with pulled back black hair standing with one arm raised above her head, looking seductively at the viewer, makeup, wearing white striped v-neck shirt with many bead necklaces around her neck and bracelets on her wrist, studio lighting, backlit, green filter, film grain, photographed on a Holga 120 CFN, 120mm, with Fuji Provia film, 100 ISO, medium format, cross-processing, filter, indoors, in Russia, photo shoot, sfw, in lomostyle

Resolution :

The model was trained on 704x704 images. But feel free to use whichever resolution you'd like.

Tags :

Note, this is not an extensive list. The model recognize tags not listed here, and some tags listed might have more weight than others—some being barely noticeable.

NSFW/SFW :

  • nsfw

  • sfw

  • erotica (usually used when image was sfw but suggestive)

  • erotic (usually used in tandem with nsfw)

Cameras :

  • Canon 3000N

Angles :

  • Front view

  • Rear angle / From behind / Back turned towards viewer

  • Side view / Side angle

  • From above / Looking down at / Top down

  • 45 degree

  • Low angle

  • High angle

  • Eye Level

  • Cowboy shot

  • Knee Level

  • Over-the-shoulder shot

  • Combinations such as :

    • Rear angle Side view

    • 45 degree rear view

    • ect..

Shot Size :

  • Extreme closeup

  • Closeup

  • Portrait (Note : can be combined with other sizes)

  • Medium closeup

  • Medium shot

  • Medium-full shot

  • Full body

Lighting :

  • Natural Light - light from a natural source. Such as,

  • Sunlight - self explanatory I hope.

  • Ambient Light -Think in the vein of the soft glow from the LED/LCD lights of your computer monitor at night.

  • Cinematic Lighting - High contrast, dramatic, deep, combo of soft light and hard light.

  • Hard Light - Light that hits the subject directly from the source, creates sharp shadows.

  • Soft Light / Diffused Soft Light - Light that is diffused before hitting the subject, creates soft shadows

  • Reflective Light - Light that reflects off of the subject and is registered by the camera.

  • Tungsten Light - The color temperature associated with incandescent light, typically 3,200K.

  • Dappled Light - Light that typically comes through gaps in a tree canopy.

  • Eyelight - A small light dedicated to adding a glint to the subjects' eyes.

  • Florescent light - Type of ambient light - think, the lightbulbs in many homes.

  • Fill Flash Lighting - Using cameras flash in low-light environment

  • More lighting terms :

    • backlit

    • side lighting

    • silhouette

    • rim lighting

Misc. Tags :

  • Scan Lines

  • Cross Processing / Cross-processed

  • Overlay Text (format = Film Overlay text: ' ')

  • Shadows :

    • Sharp Shadows

    • Soft Shadows

  • Panorama / Panoramic

  • Waist up / Waist Down

  • Bodyscape

  • Photo Type (other than portrait/full body/ect.):

    • landscape, architecture, cityscape, seascape, seaside, artistic

  • Redscale

  • Infrared

  • Tungsten film

  • Time of day:

    • morning, dawn, day, afternoon, evening, dusk, night

Webui Settings :

Clip Skip : 1

  • Settings -> Sampler parameters -> Clip skip

ETA Noise Seed Delta : 31337

  • Settings -> Sampler parameters -> Eta noise seed delta

Face Restoration : Disabled (See ADetailer)

  • IF enabled : Settings -> Face restoration -> CodeFormer -> weight = 0.8

Parameters :

  • Sampler :

    • I used a combination of Euler a, DPM++ SDE Karras for many of the sample images, but this is just personal preference.

  • Steps : Depends on the sampler, typically 20 - 35 works well.

    • If DDIM use higher steps

Hires Fix (Optional) :

  • I used x1_ITF_SkinDiffDetail_Lite_v1 which you can find - here.

  • Note : You don't need to download the .yaml, just the .pth file.

  • Install to stable-diffusion-webui -> models -> ESRGAN

  • Feel free to use any other upscaler you prefer, this was just the one I used for the sample images.

Extensions :

ADetailer :

Extension for webui that uses ultralytics to 'fix' faces/hands/body after generation.

Download here - https://github.com/Bing-su/adetailer

Read the information in the Github repo linked above for more info and installation guide.

Akashiyaki is similar to takoyaki without sauce.

It is eaten with a flavorful broth made from kelp and bonito.

In drawing by AI, the sauce and mayonnaise are added independently of the soup.

Akashiyaki is also called tamagoyaki, but dashi-maki tamago is also called tamagoyaki.

Dashi-maki tamago is a square omelet with a mottled yellow and white pattern.

Tamagodon is a cheaper version of oyakodon.

Oyakodon has green onions and chicken, but tamagodon does not.

If you don't want the AI to add extra stuff, add sauce and mayonnaise to your negative prompt.

If Takoyaki turns into a three-dimensional torus, put bagels and nipples on the negative prompt.

Middle-aged men's bulging bellies resemble takoyaki, so they are thrown into the soup.
